SQL> CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE compile_code(p_pkg_name VARCHAR2) IS
  2    v_warn_value   VARCHAR2(200);
  3    v_compile_stmt VARCHAR2(200) := 'ALTER PACKAGE '|| p_pkg_name ||' COMPILE';
  4  
  5  BEGIN
  6  
  7  -- Save and print current session settings.
  8     v_warn_value := DBMS_WARNING.GET_WARNING_SETTING_STRING;
  9     DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Current warning settings: '|| v_warn_value);
 10  
 11  -- Disable performance and print the settings.
 12     DBMS_WARNING.ADD_WARNING_SETTING_CAT('PERFORMANCE', 'DISABLE', 'SESSION');
 13     DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Modified warning settings: ' || DBMS_WARNING.GET_WARNING_SETTING_STRING);
 14  
 15  -- Compile an existing package. NOTE: Before you run the command, you must create
 16  -- the MY_PKG script found in the demo_07_33.sql. This demo script creates the MY_PKG package.
 17  
 18     EXECUTE IMMEDIATE v_compile_stmt;
 19  
 20  -- Restore original settings.
 21     DBMS_WARNING.SET_WARNING_SETTING_STRING(v_warn_value, 'SESSION');
 22  
 23  -- Prints restored orginal settings.
 24     DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Restored warning settings: '|| DBMS_WARNING.GET_WARNING_SETTING_STRING);
 25  
 26  END;
 27  /

Procedure created.

SQL> EXECUTE compile_code('DEPT_PKG');
Current warning settings: DISABLE:ALL                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       
Modified warning settings: DISABLE:ALL                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      
Restored warning settings: DISABLE:ALL                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      

PL/SQL procedure successfully completed.

SQL> EXECUTE DBMS_WARNING.SET_WARNING_SETTING_STRING('ENABLE:ALL', 'SESSION');

PL/SQL procedure successfully completed.

SQL> EXECUTE compile_code('DEPT_PKG');
Current warning settings: ENABLE:ALL                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
Modified warning settings: ENABLE:INFORMATIONAL,DISABLE:PERFORMANCE,ENABLE:SEVERE                                                                                                                                                                                                                           
Restored warning settings: ENABLE:ALL                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       

PL/SQL procedure successfully completed.

  4      INSERT INTO t(col_a) VALUES (i);
  5    EXCEPTION
  6      WHEN OTHERS THEN null;
  7    END p;
